  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BRAVE - Recognition And Valuing women&apos;s work for Care Economy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthened engagement of key influencers (Civil Society Organisations (CSOs), Women&apos;s Rights Organisations (WROs), champion policy -/decision -makers, community care champions, etc.) in support of enabling policy framework for care economy.  The project on: Building constituency for the Recognition And Valuing women&apos;s work for Care Economy (BRAVE) builds on Oxfam&apos;s years of work on unpaid care work (UCW) and contributes to strengthening gender and development work in the Philippines by shaping, informing and developing a sound policy framework for Care work in the Philippines building from the country&apos;s previous work on gender and development. Given this the project aims to inform the development of a sound, sustainable policy framework for Unpaid Care Work in the Philippines</narrative>
  </description>
